<D>__{he never does what we rehearsed. what's the point of...}
<C>__{ray}
<D>__{how does it feel?}
<C>__{john}
<D>__{great, but...}
<A>__{pam on payphone calling her friends to come.}
<C>__{pam}
<D>__{...make sure you get barb and sue anne to come. and tell them to ask for jim!}
<A>__{the manager on his way out leaning into jim's face, slyly.}
<C>__{manager}
<D>__{jim, how old are you?}
<C>__{jim}
<D>__{ah, twenty one...}
<C>__{manager}
<D>__{jesus, you're a gold mine, i will make it quick and to the point and if you repeat it i will deny it drop these guys, i will put you with some real musicians, your voice, your looks, that's what'll sell records, we'll make a million bucks. a year. goodbye. call me. i'm right. he gives jim a card and goes. pam disgusted with the type, jim laughs, likes the guy.}
